<!--526-->Aula (Starting: <!--348-->Cloud Sceptre)<br>
<!--665-->Elios<br>
<!--343-->Nimbulo (Starting: <!--356-->Shooting Star)<br>
<br>
Creatures:<br>
3x <!--329}<!--{354-->Lightning Hyren<br>
2x <!--327-->Cyclone Vashp<br>
3x <!--520-->Flutter Yup<br>
3x <!--337-->Xyx<br>
2x Collosus<br>
3x <!--664-->Shock Vashp<br>
2x <!--662-->Grand <!--328-->Epik<br>
<br>
Spells:<br>
3x <!--355-->Shockwave<br>
3x <!--356-->Shooting Star<br>
3x <!--358-->Updraft<br>
2x <!--554-->Dream Rift<br>
3x <!--670}<!--{528-->Sorreah&#39;s Dream<br>
1x <!--669-->Cataclysm<br>
<br>
Relics:<br>
1x <!--351-->Storm Ring<br>
2x <!--507-->Relic Stalker<br>
3x <!--512-->Warrior&#39;s Boots<br>
1x <!--348-->Cloud Sceptre  </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="Haettenschweiler, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif" size="5" COLOR="#000000">Strategy</Font></TD><TD><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2">Aula grabs the Cloud Sceptre and four random cards, and plays three of them, then Windsight&#39;s for even more.  Try to set up Elios as much as possible and hold any Grand Epiks you draw.  Shock Vashps work very well with Aula, as you can just bump your hand size back up again with her power.  Use the Cloud Sceptre to drop unneeded cards and get more creatures for Elios.<br>
<br>
When you flip to Elios, Dream Hard to get your hand size up, then play a Grand Epik and set your energize to eight.  The Epik will drop your energize to six, but will get six itself each turn, effectively giving you twelve energy a turn.<br>
<br>
If you have to flip to Nimbulo, work the energy reduction angle.  A Calaclysm might be in order if they took out Elios with a large swarm.<br>
<br>
Use Updraft to recycle your Collosuses and Lightning Hyrens when they get low on energy, or on the Grand Epik when it gets too high and in in danger of being Shockwaved.<br>
<br>
Sorreah&#39;s Dream works on the Xyx&#39;s Shock (3), Lightning Hyren&#39;s Shockstorm (4), Cloud Sceptre&#39;s Mindwinds (1), Nimbulo&#39;s Energy Drain (1), Aula&#39;s Windsight (2), Cyclone Vashp&#39;s Cyclone (1) and Shock Vashp&#39;s Shock (0), as well as many of your opponent&#39;s powers.  It is extremely versatile. </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="Haettenschweiler, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif" size="5" COLOR="#000000"> </Font></TD><TD><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2">DeckTech <BR> For the Players, By the Players  <BR>www.decktech.net </FONT></TD></TR></table> 
